\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"980\" height=\"721\" src=\"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.28-1024x753.jpeg\" class=\"attachment-large size-large wp-image-12319\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.28-1024x753.jpeg 1024w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.28-300x221.jpeg 300w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.28-768x565.jpeg 768w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.28-612x450.jpeg 612w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.28.jpeg 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-95f2115\" data-id=\"95f2115\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-296cee0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"296cee0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"980\" height=\"705\" src=\"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.38-1024x737.jpeg\" class=\"attachment-large size-large wp-image-12318\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.38-1024x737.jpeg 1024w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.38-300x216.jpeg 300w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.38-768x553.jpeg 768w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.38-625x450.jpeg 625w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-04-at-22.45.38.jpeg 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f411c2a e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"f411c2a\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_has_onepagescroll_dot&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-dec609c e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"dec609c\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_has_onepagescroll_dot&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-dc48bd0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"dc48bd0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3>Itinerary<\/h3><p><b>Day 1: Marrakech \u2013 Ait Bouguemez Valley<\/b><\/p><p>Transfer to the Happy Valley: Drive from Marrakech through scenic mountain roads to Ait Bouguemez, also known as the &#8220;Happy Valley.&#8221;<\/p><p>Explore the Area: Spend the afternoon exploring the lush valley, dotted with traditional Berber villages and terraced fields.<\/p><p>Overnight Stay: Stay in a guesthouse, enjoying a traditional Moroccan dinner.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>&#8212;<\/p><p><b>Day 2: Ait Bouguemez \u2013 Tarkeddit Plateau<\/b><\/p><p>Trek Begins: Start your trek with a gradual ascent through lush pastures and rocky terrain.<\/p><p>Reach Tarkeddit Plateau: Arrive at the high plateau, a stunning open area with panoramic views of the surrounding peaks.<\/p><p>Overnight Camp: Set up camp on the plateau, enjoying a peaceful evening under the stars.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>&#8212;<\/p><p><b>Day 3: Tarkeddit Plateau \u2013 Mount M\u2019Goun Summit \u2013 Oulilimte Valley<\/b><\/p><p>Summit Day: Start early to ascend Mount M\u2019Goun (4,068 meters). The climb is challenging but rewards you with breathtaking views of the Atlas Mountains and distant Sahara Desert.<\/p><p>Descend to Oulilimte Valley: After reaching the summit, descend to the beautiful Oulilimte Valley.<\/p><p>Overnight Camp: Camp by the river, surrounded by the valley&#8217;s serene landscapes.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>&#8212;<\/p><p><b>Day 4: Oulilimte Valley \u2013 Ait Imi Gorge<\/b><\/p><p>River Trekking: Follow the river through Oulilimte Valley, passing small Berber settlements and stunning landscapes.<\/p><p>Ait Imi Gorge: Trek through the dramatic Ait Imi Gorge, with its narrow passages and towering cliffs.<\/p><p>Overnight Camp: Set up camp near the gorge, enjoying the tranquility of nature.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>&#8212;<\/p><p><b>Day 5: Ait Imi Gorge \u2013 Ait Bouguemez Valley<\/b><\/p><p>Return to the Happy Valley: Continue your trek back to Ait Bouguemez, taking in the lush green terraces and traditional Berber villages.<\/p><p>Free Time: Spend the afternoon relaxing and exploring the valley.<\/p><p>Overnight Stay: Stay in a guesthouse, enjoying a celebratory dinner.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>&#8212;<\/p><p><b>Day 6: Ait Bouguemez \u2013 Marrakech<\/b><\/p><p>Drive to Marrakech: After breakfast, enjoy a scenic transfer back to Marrakech, reflecting on your incredible adventure.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>&#8212;<\/p><p><b>Highlights of the Trek<\/b><\/p><p>Summit Mount M\u2019Goun, Morocco\u2019s second-highest peak, for breathtaking views of the Atlas Mountains and Sahara Desert.<\/p><p>Explore the Ait Bouguemez Valley, known for its vibrant greenery and warm Berber hospitality.<\/p><p>Trek through diverse landscapes, including rocky plateaus, lush valleys, and dramatic gorges.<\/p><p>Camp under the stars and immerse yourself in the natural beauty of the High Atlas.<\/p><p>Interact with local Berber communities and experience their rich culture and traditions.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><p>&#8212;<\/p><p>This 6-day trek to Mount M\u2019Goun is a perfect adventure for avid trekkers, offering stunning landscapes, cultural experiences, and a true connection with Morocco\u2019s natural beauty.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Mount M\u2019Goun trek \u200b The Mount M\u2019Goun trek is a challenging and rewarding journey through the High Atlas Mountains. At 4,068 meters, M\u2019Goun is the second-highest peak in Morocco, offering breathtaking views, diverse landscapes, and a glimpse into the traditional Berber way of life. This 6-day trek is perfect for those seeking a mix of [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":5,"featured_media":0,"parent":11315,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_active":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_note":"","_monsterinsights_sitenote_category":0,"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-11592","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/11592","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/5"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=11592"}],"version-history":[{"count":26,"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/11592\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":12773,"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/11592\/revisions\/12773"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/11315"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=11592"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}